obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12934)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12934&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Sexual Harassment of`
  line `Women at Workplace (Prevention, Prohibition and Redressal) Act, 2013.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 9th December, 2013, vide notification No. S.O. 3606(E), dated 9th December, 2013, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part`
  line `II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12935)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12935&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line
  line `(a) “aggrieved woman” means—`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a workplace, a woman, of any age whether employed or not, who alleges to`
  line `have been subjected to any act of sexual harassment by the respondent;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to dwelling place or house, a woman of any age who is employed in such a`
  line `dwelling place or house;`
  line
  line `(b) “appropriate Government” means—`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a workplace which is established, owned, controlled or wholly or`
  line `substantially financed by funds provided directly or indirectly—`
  line
  line `(A) by the Central Government or the Union territory administration, the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(B) by the State Government, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any workplace not covered under sub-clause (i) and falling within its`
  line `territory, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(c) “Chairperson” means the Chairperson of the Local Complaints Committee nominated under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) “District Officer” means on officer notified under section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) "domestic worker" means a woman who is employed to do the household work in any`
  line `household for remuneration whether in cash or kind, either directly or through any agency on a`
  line `temporary, permanent, part time or full time basis, but does not include any member of the family of`
  line `the employer;`
  line
  line `(f) "employee" means a person employed at a workplace for any work on regular, temporary, ad`
  line `hoc or daily wage basis, either directly or through an agent, including a contractor, with or, without`
  line `the knowledge of the principal employer, whether for remuneration or not, or working on a voluntary`
  line `basis or otherwise, whether the terms of employment are express or implied and includes a co-worker,`
  line `a contract worker, probationer, trainee, apprentice or called by any other such name;`
  line
  line `(g) "employer" means—`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to any department, organisation, undertaking, establishment, enterprise,`
  line `institution, office, branch or unit of the appropriate Government or a local authority, the head of`
  line `that department, organisation, undertaking, establishment, enterprise, institution, office, branch or`
  line `unit or such other officer as the appropriate Government or the local authority, as the case may`
  line `be, may by an order specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(ii) in any workplace not covered under sub-clause (i), any person responsible for the`
  line `management, supervision and control of the workplace.`
  line
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this sub-clause “management” includes the person or`
  line `board or committee responsible for formulation and administration of polices for such`
  line organisation;
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to workplace covered under sub-clauses (i) and (ii), the person discharging`
  line `contractual obligations with respect to his or her employees;`
  line
  line `(iv) in relation to a dwelling place or house, a person or a household who employs or benefits`
  line `from the employment of domestic worker, irrespective of the number, time period or type of such`
  line `worker employed, or the nature of the employment or activities performed by the domestic`
  line worker;
  line
  line `(h) “Internal Committee” means an Internal Complaints Committee constituted under section 4;`
  line
  line `(i) “Local Committee” means the Local Complaints Committee constituted under section 6;`
  line
  line `(j) “Member” means a Member of the Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as the case`
  line `may be;`
  line
  line `(k) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) “Presiding Officer” means the Presiding Officer of the Internal Complaints Committee`
  line `nominated under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(m) “respondent’ means a person against whom the aggrieved woman has made a complaint`
  line `under section 9;`
  line
  line `(n) “sexual harassment” includes any one or more of the following unwelcome acts or behavior`
  line `(whether directly or by implication) namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) physical contact and advances; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a demand or request for sexual favours; or`
  line
  line `(iii) making sexually coloured remarks; or`
  line
  line `(iv) showing pornography; or`
  line
  line `(v) any other unwelcome physical, verbal or non-verbal conduct of sexual nature;`
  line
  line `(o) “workplace” includes—`
  line
  line `(i) any department, organisation, undertaking, establishment, enterprise, institution, office,`
  line `branch or unit which is established, owned, controlled or wholly or substantially financed by`
  line `funds provided directly or indirectly by the appropriate Government or the local authority or a`
  line `Government company or a corporation or a co-operative society;`
  line
  line `(ii) any private sector organisation or a private venture, undertaking, enterprise, institution,`
  line `establishment, society, trust, non-governmental organisation, unit or service provider carrying on`
  line `commercial, professional, vocational, educational, entertainmental, industrial, health services or`
  line `financial activities including production, supply, sale, distribution or service;`
  line
  line `(iii) hospitals or nursing homes;`
  line
  line `(iv) any sports institute, stadium, sports complex or competition or games venue, whether`
  line `residential or not used for training, sports or other activities relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(v) any place visited by the employee arising out of or during the course of employment`
  line `including transportation by the employer for undertaking such journey;`
  line
  line `(vi) a dwelling place or a house;`
  line
  line `(p) “unorganised sector” in relation to a workplace means an enterprise owned by individuals or`
  line `self-employed workers and engaged in the production or sale of goods or providing service of any`
  line `kind whatsoever, and where the enterprise employs workers, the number of such workers is less than`
  line ten.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12936)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Prevention of sexual harassment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12936&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No woman shall be subjected to sexual harassment at any`
  line workplace.
  line
  line `(2) The following circumstances, among other circumstances, if it occurs, or is present in relation to`
  line `or connected with any act or behavior of sexual harassment may amount to sexual harassment:—`
  line
  line `(i) implied or explicit promise of preferential treatment in her employment; or`
  line
  line `(ii) implied or explicit threat of detrimental treatment in her employment ; or`
  line
  line `(iii) implied or explicit threat about her present or future employment status; or`
  line
  line `(iv) interference with her work or creating an intimidating or offensive or hostile work`
  line `environment for her; or`
  line
  line `(v) humiliating treatment likely to affect her health or safety.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12937)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of Internal Complaints Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12937&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every employer of a workplace shall, by`
  line `an order in writing, constitute a Committee to be known as the “Internal Complaints Committee”:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the offices or administrative units of the workplace are located at different places`
  line `or divisional or sub-divisional level, the Internal Committee shall be constituted at all administrative units`
  line `or offices.`
  line
  line `(2) The Internal Committees shall consist of the following members to be nominated by the`
  line `employer, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a Presiding Officer who shall be a woman employed at a senior level at workplace from`
  line `amongst the employees:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case a senior level woman employee is not available, the Presiding Officer shall`
  line `be nominated from other offices or administrative units of the workplace referred to in sub-section(1):`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case the other offices or administrative units of the workplace do not`
  line `have a senior level woman employee, the Presiding Officer shall be nominated from any other`
  line `workplace of the same employer or other department or organisation;`
  line
  line `(b) not less than two Members from amongst employees preferably committed to the cause of`
  line `women or who have had experience in social work or have legal knowledge;`
  line
  line `(c) one member from amongst non-governmental organisations or associations committed to the`
  line `cause of women or a person familiar with the issues relating to sexual harassment:`
  line
  line `Provided that at least one-half of the total Members so nominated shall be women.`
  line
  line `(3) The Presiding Officer and every Member of the Internal Committee shall hold office for such`
  line `period, not exceeding three years, from the date of their nomination as may be specified by the employer.`
  line
  line `(4) The Member appointed from amongst the non-governmental organisations or associations shall be`
  line `paid such fees or allowances for holding the proceedings of the Internal Committee, by the employer, as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Presiding Officer or any Member of the Internal Committee,—`
  line
  line `(a) contravenes the provisions of section 16; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted for an offence or an inquiry into an offence under any law for the time`
  line `being in force is pending against him; or`
  line
  line `(c) he has been found quilty in any disciplinary proceedings or a disciplinary proceeding is`
  line `pending against him; or`
  line
  line `(d) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line interest,
  line
  line `such Presiding Officer or Member, as the case may be, shall be removed from the Committee and the`
  line `vacancy so created or any casual vacancy shall be filled by fresh nomination in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12938)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Notification of District Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12938&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may notify a District Magistrate`
  line `or Additional District Magistrate or the Collector or Deputy Collector as a District Officer for every`
  line `District to exercise powers or discharge functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12939)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Constitution and jurisdiction of Local Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12939&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `6. Constitution and jurisdiction of^ 1`
  line `[Local Committee].—(1) Every District Officer shall constitute`
  line `in the district concerned, a committee to be known as the “^1`
  line `[Local Committee]” to receive complaints of sexual harassment from establishments where the ^2`
  line `[Internal Committee] has not been constituted due to`
  line `having less than ten workers or if the complaint is against the employer himself.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Officer shall designate one nodal officer in every block, taluka and tehsil in rural or`
  line `tribal area and ward or municipality in the urban area, to receive complaints and forward the same to the`
  line `concerned ^3`
  line `[Local Committee] within a period of seven days.`
  line
  line `(3) The jurisdiction of the ^3`
  line `[Local Committee] shall extend to the areas of the district where it is`
  line constituted.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2016, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "Local Complaints Committee" (w.e.f. 6-5-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2016, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "Internal Complaints Committee" (w.e.f. 6-5-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid0231., for "Local Complaints Committee" (w.e.f. 6-5-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12940)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Composition tenure and other terms and conditions of Local Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid., for "Local Complaints Committee" (w.e.f. 6-5-2016)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12940&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `7. Composition, tenure and other terms and conditions of ^1`
  line `[Local Committee].—(1) The ^1`
  line
  line [Local
  line `Committee] shall consist of the following members to be nominated by the District Officer, namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson to be nominated from amongst the eminent women in the field of social work`
  line `and committed to the cause of women;`
  line
  line `(b) one Member to be nominated from amongst the women working in block, taluka or tehsil or`
  line `ward or municipality in the district;`
  line
  line `(c) two Members, of whom at least one shall be a woman, to be nominated from amongst such`
  line `non-governmental organisations or associations committed to the cause of women or a person`
  line `familiar with the issues relating to sexual harassment, which may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that at least one of the nominees should, preferably, have a background in law or legal`
  line `knowledge:`
  line
  line `Provided further that at least one of the nominees shall be a woman belonging to the Scheduled`
  line `Castes or the Scheduled Tribes or the Other Backward Classes or minority community notified by the`
  line `Central Government, from time to time;`
  line
  line `(d) the concerned officer dealing with the social welfare or women and child development in the`
  line `district, shall be a member ex officio.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and every Member of the Local Committee shall hold office for such period, not`
  line `exceeding three years, form the date of their appointment as may be specified by the District Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Chairperson or any Member of the ^1`
  line
  line `[Local Committee]—`
  line
  line `(a) contravenes the provisions of section 16; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted for an offence or an inquiry into an offence under any law for the time`
  line `being in force is pending against him; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been found guilty in any disciplinary proceedings or a disciplinary proceeding is pending`
  line `against him; or`
  line
  line `(d) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line interest,
  line
  line `such Chairperson or Member, as the case may be, shall be removed from the Committee and the vacancy`
  line `so created or any casual vacancy shall be filled by fresh nomination in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson or Members of the Local Committee other than the Members nominated under`
  line `clauses (b) and (d) of sub-section (1) shall be entitled to such fees or allowances for holding the`
  line `proceedings of the Local Committee as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12941)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Grants and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12941&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after due appropriation made by Parliament`
  line `by law in this behalf, make to the State Government grants of such sums of money as the Central Government my think fit, for being utilised for the payment of fees or allowances referred to in subsection`
  line `(4) of section 7.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may set up an agency and transfer the grants made under sub-section (1) to`
  line `that agency.`
  line
  line `(3) The agency shall pay to the District Officer, such sums as may be required for the payment of fees`
  line `or allowances referred to in sub-section (4) of section 7.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the agency referred to in sub-section (2) shall be maintained and audited in such`
  line `manner as may, in consultation with the Accountant General of the State, be prescribed and the person`
  line `holding the custody of the accounts of the agency shall furnish, to the State Government, before such`
  line `date, as may be prescribed, its audited copy of accounts together with auditors' report thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12942)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Complaint of sexual harassment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12942&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any aggrieved woman may make, in writing, a complaint`
  line `of sexual harassment at workplace to the Internal Committee if so constituted, or the Local Committee, in`
  line `case it is not so constituted, within a period of three months from the date of incident and in case of a`
  line `series of incidents, within a period of three months from the date of last incident:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such complaint cannot be made in writing, the Presiding Officer or any Member`
  line `of the Internal Committee or the Chairperson or any Member of the Local Committee, as the case may be,`
  line `shall render all reasonable assistance to the woman for making the complaint in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Internal Committee or, as the case may be, the Local Committee may, for`
  line `the reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the time limit not exceeding three months , if it is satisfied`
  line `that the circumstances were such which prevented the woman from filing a complaint within the said`
  line period.
  line
  line `(2) Where the aggrieved woman is unable to make a complaint on account of her physical or mental`
  line `incapacity or death or otherwise, her legal heir or such other person as may be prescribed may make a`
  line `complaint under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12943)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Conciliation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12943&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Internal Committee or, as the case may be, the Local Committee, may,`
  line `before initiating an inquiry under section 11 and at the request of the aggrieved woman take steps to settle`
  line `the matter between her and the respondent through conciliation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no monetary settlement shall be made as a basis of conciliation.`
  line
  line `(2) Where settlement has been arrived at under sub-section (1), the Internal Committee or the Local`
  line `Committee, as the case may be, shall record the settlement so arrived and forward the same to the`
  line `employer or the District Officer to take action as specified in the recommendation.`
  line
  line `(3) The Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as the case may be, shall provide the copies of`
  line `the settlement as recorded under sub-section (2) to the aggrieved woman and the respondent.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a settlement is arrived at under sub-section (1), no further inquiry shall be conducted by the`
  line `Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12944)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Inquiry into complaint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12944&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 10, the Internal Committee or`
  line `the Local Committee, as the case may be, shall, where the respondent is an employee, proceed to make`
  line `inquiry into the complaint in accordance with the provisions of the service rules applicable to the`
  line `respondent and where no such rules exist, in such manner as may be prescribed or in case of a domestic`
  line `worker, the Local Committee shall, if prima facie case exist, forward the complaint to the police, within a`
  line `period of seven days for registering the case under section 509 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and`
  line `any other relevant provisions of the said Code where applicable:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the aggrieved woman informs the Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as`
  line `the case may be, that any term or condition of the settlement arrived at under sub-section (2) of section 10`
  line `has not been complied with by the respondent, the Internal Committee or the Local Committee shall`
  line `proceed to make an inquiry into the complaint or, as the case may be, forward the complaint to the police:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where both the parties are employees, the parties shall, during the course of`
  line `inquiry, be given an opportunity of being heard and a copy of the findings shall be made available to both`
  line `the parties enabling them to make representation against the findings before the Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 509 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), the`
  line `court may, when the respondent is convicted of the offence, order payment of such sums as it may`
  line `consider appropriate, to the aggrieved woman by the respondent, having regard to the provisions of`
  line `section 15.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of making an inquiry under sub-section (1), the Internal Committee or the Local`
  line `Committee, as the case may be, shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) when trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents; and`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The inquiry under sub-section (1) shall be completed within a period of ninety days.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12945)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Action during pendency of inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12945&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) During the pendency of an inquiry on a written`
  line `request made by the aggrieved woman, the Internal Committee or the local Committee, as the case may`
  line `be, may recommend to the employer to—`
  line
  line `(a) transfer the aggrieved woman or the respondent to any other workplace; or`
  line
  line `(b) grant leave to the aggrieved woman up to a period of three months; or`
  line
  line `(c) grant such other relief to the aggrieved woman a may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The leave granted to the aggrieved woman under this section shall be in addition to the leave she`
  line `would be otherwise entitled.`
  line
  line `(3) On the recommendation of the Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as the case may be,`
  line `under sub-section (1), the employer shall implement the recommendations made under sub-section (1)`
  line `and send the report of such implementation to the Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12946)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Inquiry report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12946&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the completion of an inquiry under this Act, the Internal Committee or`
  line `the Local Committee, as the case may be, shall provide a report of its findings to the employer, or as the`
  line `case may be, the District Officer within a period of ten days from the date of completion of the inquiry`
  line `and such report be made available to the concerned parties.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as the case may be, arrives at the`
  line `conclusion that the allegation against the respondent has not been proved, it shall recommend to the`
  line `employer and the District Officer that no action is required to be taken in the matter.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as the case may be, arrives at the`
  line `conclusion that the allegation against the respondent has been proved, it shall recommend to the employer`
  line `or the District Officer, as the case may be—`
  line
  line `(i) to take action for sexual harassment as a misconduct in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `service rules applicable to the respondent or where no such service rules have been made, in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(ii) to deduct, notwithstanding anything in the service rules applicable to the respondent, from the`
  line `salary or wages of the respondent such sum as it may consider appropriate to be paid to the aggrieved`
  line `woman or to her legal heirs, as it may determine, in accordance with the provisions of section 15:`
  line
  line `Provide that in case the employer is unable to make such deduction from the salary of the`
  line `respondent due to his being absent from duty or cessation of employment it may direct to the`
  line `respondent to pay such sum to the aggrieved woman:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case the respondent fails to pay the sum referred to in clause (ii), the`
  line `Internal Committee or as, the case may be, the Local Committee may forward the order for recovery`
  line `of the sum as an arrear of land revenue to the concerned District Officer.`
  line
  line `(4) The employer or the District Officer shall act upon the recommendation within sixty days of its`
  line `receipt by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12947)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Punishment for false or malicious complaint and false evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12947&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Internal`
  line `Committee or the Local Committee, as the case may be, arrives at a conclusion that the allegation against`
  line `the respondent is malicious or the aggrieved woman or any other person making the complaint has made`
  line `the complaint knowing it to be false or the aggrieved woman or any other person making the complaint`
  line `has produced any forged or misleading document, it may recommend to the employer or the District`
  line `Officer, as the case may be, to take action against the woman or the person who has made the complaint`
  line `under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 9, as the case may be, in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the service rules applicable to her or him or where no such service rules exist, in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that a mere inability to substantiate a complaint or provide adequate proof need not attract`
  line `action against the complainant under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the malicious intent on part of the complainant shall be established after an`
  line `inquiry in accordance with the procedure prescribed, before any action is recommended.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as the case may be, arrives at a conclusion`
  line `that during the inquiry any witness has given false evidence or produced any forged or misleading`
  line `document, it may recommend to the employer of the witness or the District Officer, as the case may be, to`
  line `take action in accordance with the provisions of the service rules applicable to the said witness or where`
  line `no such service rules exist, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12948)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Determination of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12948&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of determining the sums to be paid to the`
  line `aggrieved woman under clause (ii) of sub-section (3) of section 13, the Internal Committee or the Local`
  line `Committee, as the case may be, shall have regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) the mental trauma, pain, suffering and emotional distress caused to the aggrieved woman;`
  line
  line `(b) the loss in the career opportunity due to the incident of sexual harassment;`
  line
  line `(c) medical expenses incurred by the victim for physical or psychiatric treatment;`
  line
  line `(d) the income and financial status of the respondent;`
  line
  line `(e) feasibility of such payment in lump sum or in instalments.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12949)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Prohibition of publication or making known contents of complaint and inquiry proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12949&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Right to Information Act, 2005 (22 of 2005),`
  line `the contents of the complaint made under section 9, the identity and addresses of the aggrieved woman,`
  line `respondent and witnesses, any information relating to conciliation and inquiry proceedings,`
  line
  line `recommendations of the Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as the case may be, and the action`
  line `taken by the employer or the District Officer under the provisions of this Act shall not be published,`
  line `communicated or made known to the public, press and media in any manner:`
  line
  line `Provided that information may be disseminated regarding the justice secured to any vicitim of sexual`
  line `harassment under this Act without disclosing the name, address, identity or any other particulars`
  line `calculated to lead to the identification of the aggrieved woman and witnesses.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12950)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Penalty for publication or making known contents of complaint and inquiry proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12950&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Where any person entrusted with the duty to handle or deal with the complaint, inquiry or any`
  line `recommendations or action to be taken under the provisions of this Act, contravenes the provisions of`
  line `section 16, he shall be liable for penalty in accordance with the provisions of the service rules applicable`
  line `to the said person or where no such service rules exist, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12951)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12951&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved from the recommendations made under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 13 or under clause (i) or clause (ii) of sub-section (3) of section 13 or sub-section (1) or subsection`
  line `(2) of section 14 or section 17 or non-implementation of such recommendations may prefer an`
  line `appeal to the court or tribunal in accordance with the provisions of the service rules applicable to the said`
  line `person or where no such service rules exist then, without prejudice to provisions contained in any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, the person aggrieved may prefer an appeal in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The appeal under sub-section (1) shall be preferred within a period of ninety days of the`
  line recommendations.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12952)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Duties of employer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12952&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Every employer shall—`
  line
  line `(a) provide a safe working environment at the workplace with shall include safety from the`
  line `persons coming into contact at the workplace;`
  line
  line `(b) display at any conspicuous place in the workplace, the penal consequences of sexual`
  line `harassments; and the order constituting, the Internal Committee under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) organise workshops and awareness programmes at regular intervals for sensitising the`
  line `employees with the provisions of the Act and orientation programmes for the members of the Internal`
  line `Committee in the manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(d) provide necessary facilities to the Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as the case`
  line `may be, for dealing with the complaint and conducting an inquiry;`
  line
  line `(e) assist in securing the attendance of respondent and witnesses before the Internal Committee or`
  line `the Local Committee, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(f) make available such information to the Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as the`
  line `case be, as it may require having regard to the complaint made under sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(g) provide assistance to the woman if she so chooses to file a complaint in relation to the offence`
  line `under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(h) cause to initiate action, under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, against the perpetrator, or if the aggrieved woman so desires, where the perpetrator is`
  line `not an employee, in the workplace at which the incident of sexual harassment took place;`
  line
  line `(i) treat sexual harassment as a misconduct under the service rules and initiate action for such`
  line misconduct;
  line
  line `(j) monitor the timely submission of reports by the Internal Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (12953)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Duties and powers of District Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12953&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The District Officer shall, —`
  line
  line `(a) monitor the timely submission of report furnished by the Local Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) take such measures as may be necessary for engaging non-governmental organisations for`
  line `creation of awareness on sexual harassment and the rights of the women.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (12954)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Committee to submit annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12954&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Internal Committee or the Local Committee, as`
  line `the case may be, shall in each calendar year prepare, in such form and at such time as may be prescribed,`
  line `an annual report and submit the same to the employer and the District Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Officer shall forward a brief report on the annual reports received under sub-section`
  line `(1) to the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (12955)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Employer to include information in annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12955&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The employer shall include in its report`
  line `the number of cases filed, if any, and their disposal under this Act in the annual report of his organisation`
  line `or where no such report is required to be prepared, intimate such number of cases, if any, to the District`
  line Officer.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (12956)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Appropriate Government to monitor implementation and maintain data.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12956&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate`
  line `Government shall monitor the implementation of this Act and maintain date on the number of cases filed`
  line `and disposed of in respect of all cases of sexual harassment at workplace.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (12957)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Appropriate Government to take measures to publicise the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2016, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "Local Complaints Committee" (w.e.f. 6-5-2016)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12957&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate`
  line `Government may, subject to the availability of financial and other resources, —`
  line
  line `(a) develop relevant information, education, communication and training materials, and organise`
  line `awareness programmes, to advance the understanding of the public of the provisions of this Act`
  line `providing for protection against sexual harassment of woman at workplace;`
  line
  line `(b) formulate orientation and training programmes for the members of the ^1`
  line `[Local Committee].`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (12958)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to call for information and inspection of records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12958&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government, on`
  line `being satisfied that it is necessary in the public interest or in the interest of women employees at a`
  line `workplace to do so, by order in writing,—`
  line
  line `(a) call upon any employer or District Officer to furnish in writing such information relating to`
  line `sexual harassment as it may require;`
  line
  line `(b) authorise any officer to make inspection of the records and workplace in relation to sexual`
  line `harassment, who shall submit a report of such inspection to it within such period as may be specified`
  line `in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Every employer and District Officer shall produce on demand before the officer making the`
  line `inspection all information, records and other documents in his custody having a bearing on the subject`
  line `matter of such inspection.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (12959)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Penalty for non-compliance with provisions of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12959&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the employer fails to—`
  line
  line `(a) constitute an Internal Committee under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) take action under sections 13, 14 and 22; and`
  line
  line `(c) contravenes or attempts to contravene or abets contravention of other provisions of this Act or`
  line `any rules made thereunder,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) If any employer, after having been previously convicted of an offence punishable under this Act`
  line `subsequently commits and is convicted of the same offence, he shall be liable to—`
  line
  line `(i) twice the punishment, which might have been imposed on a first conviction, subject to the`
  line `punishment being maximum provided for the same offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case a higher punishment is prescribed under any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, for the offence for which the accused is being prosecuted, the court shall take due cognizance`
  line `of the same while awarding the punishment;`
  line
  line `(ii) cancellation, of his licence or withdrawal, or non-renewal, or approval, or cancellation of the`
  line `registration, as the case may be, by the Government or local authority required for carrying on his`
  line `business or activity.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (12960)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Cognizance of offence by courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12960&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable`
  line `under this Act or any rules made thereunder, save on a complaint made by the aggrieved woman or any`
  line `person authorised by the Internal Committee or Local Committee in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class`
  line `shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every offence under this Act shall be non-cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (12961)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Act not in derogation of any other law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12961&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to and`
  line `not in derogation of the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (12962)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power of appropriate Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12962&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the fees or allowances to be paid to the Members under sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) nomination of members under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the fees or allowances to be paid to the Chairperson, and Members under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the person who may make complaint under sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of inquiry under sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(f) the powers for making an inquiry under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) the relief to be recommended under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of action to be taken under clause (i) of sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of action to be taken under sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of action to be taken under section 17;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of appeal under sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of organising workshops, awareness programmes for sensitising the employees and`
  line `orientation programmes for the members of the Internal Committee under clause (c) of section 19;`
  line and
  line
  line `(m) the form and time for preparation of annual report by Internal Committee and the Local`
  line `Committee under sub-section (1) of section 21.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
  line
  line `(4) Any rule made under sub-section (4) of section 8 by the State Government shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or`
  line `where such Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (12963)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213&sectionId=12963&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00009_201314_1517807327213
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years`
  line `from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
